To check if AWS CLI is configured or not, use command aws -version .

If not installed, follow below steps:

#Installing AWS CLI on Ubuntu 22.04
sudo apt update
sudo apt install unzip
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
aws --version

After Install, configure AWS using below:

aws configure

#Enter your AWS Access Key ID, Secret Access Key, Region & Output format as JSON when prompted
